<br>
Klingon, and Tolkein's qenya, are fully developed languages with detailed grammar and rules, and well-developed vocabularies.  It's theoretically possible to learn to speak them correctly and consistently, and hold relatively complex conversations in them.  (Tolkein was in fact a linguist and the detail of his languages shows this.)<br>
<br>
It's not possible to speak Drow and communicate anything more than stock phrases either clearly or consistently.  The most you can do is throw in the odd word or phrase.<br>
<br>
Some common phrases I hear around Neriak...<br>
<br>
Vendui - hello<br>
Vedaust - goodbye<br>
Aluve - (either hello or good bye, something like 'salut' in French)<br>
Xas - yes<br>
Nau - no, not<br>
Ussta - my<br>
Abbil - friend<br>
Bel'la dos - thank you<br>
<br>
Obviously, EQ Teir'dal are not the same as AD&amp;D Drow, so some people think these phrases aren't appropriate for Teir'dal to use, some do.  Given that Verant hasn't created another language for Teir'dal to use instead of drow, I think the odd word of Drow throws in a little foreign atmosphere, so why not. <p><table border=0><tr><td width=20%><img src="http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/didi/a_didisig.gif" height=120 width=120></td><td><FONT FACE="Tempus Sans ITC" SIZE="2">
